,enc or necro(Im not a fuggin wizard) or fruity ranger(wtf im not a druid!).<br><br>C. Ask for the port. Now that youve gone thru this work, you want to make sure you close the deal. Remember, you are asking someone a favor, they dont owe you a @#%$ damn port just because they happen to play a certain class.<br><br><i>99% of the time you will get denied a port if you approach the person the wrong way. DO NOT beat around the bush, this wastes your time and their time. Every wiz/dru above lvl 29 just like a cleric, knows that a random "Hi how are you doing, are you busy?" is a request for a port or TL. </i>If you are in a dungeon, always assume  the wiz/dru are grouped unless you see them sitting at the zone in. Never ever send a tell to a dru/wiz sitting in another zone for a port. This is just rude and pretty stupid, unless you know the person or are offering 150p or more for a swift port.<br><br><b>Now to ask for the port, you can either send the dru/wiz a direct tell like this. /tell "Could ya port/tl me to Location A for X amount of platnium, I have fragment for you as well.</b><br><br>X amount of platnium=1 or 2 zones away-50p<br>Outside of the current contitnent to another-70P<br>Full service port with some grinning  dru/wiz happily buffing you with invis/sow/lev and will most often run to your location and pick you up-100p<br>Raid,Rare spawn is waiting for me-150p increase in 25p increments until you find your ride.<br><br>In zones like Dreadlands,Greater Faydark, East Commonlands 100p will automatically result in 3-4 tells from willing dru/wiz.<br><br>If the person denys you a port, use the /auc X amount of platnium to locatin A, accordingly. <br><br>D. Donts.<br><b>Never expect a port because someone is a wizard or druid.</b><br>Never argue with somone because you are denied a port.<br>Learn to ignore rude responses, however note that persons name for future CR's.<br>Never spam a request for a port in chat.<br>If you need a port for CR, run your naked ass to the bank and pay for it, your corpse is worth it.<br>Never expect a port because your cat died, your on CR, your to dumb to bind, your girlfriend is waiting for you etc etc, ask for a port nicely and treat the porter with respect, repeat business is good for both parties.<br>Never ask for a port in another zone when you are not at the portal, in fact I would advise rarely asking for a port from someone not in the same zone as you unless they are friends or you will compensate them well.<br>Never say Will Pay, Will Donate,WTB, use specific amounts to the the proper response.<br>Remeber TL's to bind or Dreadland do not require a fragment. Dont let wizards pass the no frag excuse on you, however you dont want to start a pointless argument either.  A cheap TL to DL then buying another port  could be your best bet. <b>However, if you have a fragment this will suprise and shock 95% of wizards, and usally get a positive response from a port request.</b><br>Dont use the /split command to pay, pay them in the trade window.<br>Pay for the ride, dont expect a trip then pay afterwards, even a 50 cent bus token doesnt work that way.<br><br>In closing, if you have money sitting in the bank(5k or more), like experiencing the game instead of waiting/begging/relying on other people, then enjoy this proactive approach to travelling Norrath!<br><br><i>Helped language filter a bit.  --Gyorg</i> <p><P><center><font face ="Verdana,Arial" size="3" color="red"><b> Rodcet Nife Ring Warden</b> </font><br><a href = http://http://altereddestiny.net><img src="http://hoels76.homestead.com/files/vale.jpg" alt="Rogues do it better from behind!" border="0"></a><br><small><b><font color= "yellow"><br> "Nicotine is not addictive" Tobacco Industry<br>"Rogues are a balanced class"-Gordon<br><a href="http://hoels76.tripod.com/wixsig.htm">My Sigs</a></small></font></center></b></p> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicPr